OL,3,CTram passenger involved in fatal
OL,4,Cstruggle released without charge
OL,6,FCity Superintendent Chris Pearson
OL,7,Fsaid: "Our thoughts remain with the
OL,8,Ffamily, and everyone affected by this
OL,9,Ftragic and deeply distressing
OL,10,Fincident, which resulted in the loss
OL,11,Fof a young man's life.
OL,13,F"Following a meticulous investigation,
OL,14,Fand after seeking early investigative
OL,15,Fadvice from the Crown Prosecution
OL,16,FService (CPS), we have concluded that
OL,17,Fa tram passenger acted in self-defence
OL,18,Fwhen he was attacked by a man with a
OL,19,Fknife.
